  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Since the outbreak of coronavirus disease - COVID-19 pandemic, most attention has focused on
      mode of transmission, clinical picture of the disease, treatment and prevention. In the
      coming weeks and months emphasis will gradually involve the post- acute care of COVID-19
      survivors. It is anticipated that COVID-19 may have major impact on physical, cognitive,
      mental, social health status even in patients with mild disease. Moreover, pulmonary,
      radiologic, laboratory, sleep issues remain to be addressed
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
